WEBVTT

1
00:00:05.480 --> 00:00:06.680
CONNOR: 'Jason Morgan.

2
00:00:08.280 --> 00:00:09.800
'Rob Wright.'

3
00:00:11.040 --> 00:00:12.576
Who the hell is he?

4
00:00:12.600 --> 00:00:14.856
We are definitely
in serial-killer territory.

5
00:00:14.880 --> 00:00:17.056
MONICA: 'They had another phone.'
PHONE BEEPS.

6
00:00:17.080 --> 00:00:18.336
'Just like Rob.'

7
00:00:18.360 --> 00:00:19.896
'Did you look into them?'

8
00:00:19.920 --> 00:00:22.336
The Burning Light.
they've moved to the Isle of Mull.

9
00:00:22.360 --> 00:00:24.976
It's for the best
that I take Lucy to him.

10
00:00:25.000 --> 00:00:26.200
GRUNTING

11
00:00:27.720 --> 00:00:28.840
And what about your mummy?

12
00:00:29.880 --> 00:00:32.000
She's a police officer? Mm-hm.

13
00:00:34.280 --> 00:00:36.640
Was she the one that told you
about the poison?

14
00:00:38.800 --> 00:00:40.376
MONICA: These were
inside the victims.

15
00:00:40.400 --> 00:00:42.016
I told you before he disappeared

16
00:00:42.040 --> 00:00:44.176
that he was holding a stone
just like that.

17
00:00:44.200 --> 00:00:47.376
You didn't listen.
I trusted you. Monica.

18
00:00:47.400 --> 00:00:50.176
Hey. mother. Nichol?

19
00:00:50.200 --> 00:00:53.160
Could join me on the hunt tomorrow?
Is this cos of what the police said?

20
00:00:54.720 --> 00:00:58.160
I'm not weak.
I can look after myself.

21
00:01:44.760 --> 00:01:46.016
Ah!

22
00:01:46.040 --> 00:01:47.200
INTRUDER GRUNTS

23
00:01:52.640 --> 00:01:53.880
Ah!

24
00:01:57.960 --> 00:01:59.480
Ugh! Ah!

25
00:02:10.600 --> 00:02:12.080
Argh!

26
00:02:17.840 --> 00:02:19.400
GRUNT. THUD

27
00:02:38.960 --> 00:02:40.000
Help me!

28
00:02:49.680 --> 00:02:51.656
MONICA GASPS Monica. It's OK.

29
00:02:51.680 --> 00:02:53.016
It's me. Hi.

30
00:02:53.040 --> 00:02:56.560
Mum? What?
Your phone has been going non-stop.

31
00:02:57.760 --> 00:02:59.056
Shit.

32
00:02:59.080 --> 00:03:00.976
I didn't wanna wake you.

33
00:03:01.000 --> 00:03:03.096
The Crawfords turned up. and I...

34
00:03:03.120 --> 00:03:05.496
Ugh. Morning.

35
00:03:05.520 --> 00:03:08.416
Another? Yeah. sadly.

36
00:03:08.440 --> 00:03:10.616
This kid managed to escape. It's...

37
00:03:10.640 --> 00:03:13.096
It's. erm... It's quite a trek.

38
00:03:13.120 --> 00:03:16.800
I'll. er. wait in the car.
Let you get...

39
00:03:17.880 --> 00:03:19.640
Mm. Yep. See you.

40
00:03:23.760 --> 00:03:25.320
Mum. you're hovering. Speak.

41
00:03:26.440 --> 00:03:29.520
So. I saw Philly yesterday
at the play park.

42
00:03:30.640 --> 00:03:33.416
SIGHS She...

43
00:03:33.440 --> 00:03:34.656
What?

44
00:03:34.680 --> 00:03:37.176
Well. it ended with me slapping her.

45
00:03:37.200 --> 00:03:39.096
Slapping her?
I don't know what came over me.

46
00:03:39.120 --> 00:03:41.976
I just saw red and...
How could you do something so mad?

47
00:03:42.000 --> 00:03:44.256
Mad? She tried to take Lucy.

48
00:03:44.280 --> 00:03:46.296
What?! Snatch her. Yeah.

49
00:03:46.320 --> 00:03:48.096
Don't call me mad.
At least start with that.

50
00:03:48.120 --> 00:03:49.376
You brought her into our lives

51
00:03:49.400 --> 00:03:52.136
when you were investigating
that cult. Careful.

52
00:03:52.160 --> 00:03:54.056
True. Monica.

53
00:03:54.080 --> 00:03:55.856
You know
she's completely brainwashed.

54
00:03:55.880 --> 00:03:57.736
just like you were
after they sucked you in.

55
00:03:57.760 --> 00:03:59.696
Mum. You were at rock bottom.

56
00:03:59.720 --> 00:04:01.576
You were penniless.
You were pregnant.

57
00:04:01.600 --> 00:04:04.096
But because you had me
to help you through.

58
00:04:04.120 --> 00:04:05.736
you didn't end up like Philly.

59
00:04:05.760 --> 00:04:08.216
So don't make out
that I am the villain here.

60
00:04:08.240 --> 00:04:11.000
Oh. no. I know
that's my role in this family.

61
00:04:12.360 --> 00:04:14.576
Oh. no. that...
That's not what I meant.

62
00:04:14.600 --> 00:04:16.376
No. no.
Clearly been thinking it a while.

63
00:04:16.400 --> 00:04:18.576
No. I didn't mean it
to come out that way.

64
00:04:18.600 --> 00:04:22.216
Look. Mum. later. Tonight.

65
00:04:22.240 --> 00:04:24.816
We'll talk about this tonight.
Yeah. OK.

66
00:04:24.840 --> 00:04:27.280
What do you want me to do?
Keep Lucy at home today.

67
00:04:28.600 --> 00:04:30.040
Absolutely.

68
00:04:31.400 --> 00:04:33.336
'Inspector Hately.
it's all well and good

69
00:04:33.360 --> 00:04:35.056
'you telling people to stay calm.

70
00:04:35.080 --> 00:04:37.456
'but there is a maniac
on the loose killing young men.'

71
00:04:37.480 --> 00:04:41.136
'I understand their concern.'
'They don't want your understanding.

72
00:04:41.160 --> 00:04:43.640
'They want to know when you're
going to stop this monster.'

73
00:04:46.280 --> 00:04:49.856
First response again.
Not this time.

74
00:04:49.880 --> 00:04:53.696
He fled to a garage about
half a mile or so down the road.

75
00:04:53.720 --> 00:04:55.256
Member of staff called it in.

76
00:04:55.280 --> 00:04:56.696
By the time units got here.

77
00:04:56.720 --> 00:04:58.816
they realised
what they were dealing with.

78
00:04:58.840 --> 00:05:01.680
So we probably lost six.
seven hours.

79
00:05:04.040 --> 00:05:05.656
What's his recollection like?

80
00:05:05.680 --> 00:05:08.480
Part of me thinks it'd be easier
for him if it wasn't so good.

81
00:05:09.600 --> 00:05:11.200
Want me to introduce you? Mm.

82
00:05:15.160 --> 00:05:19.376
Scott. this is Detective Inspector
Monica Kennedy.

83
00:05:19.400 --> 00:05:21.960
She'd just like to ask you
a few questions. Is that OK?

84
00:05:23.920 --> 00:05:25.656
Hi. Scott.

85
00:05:25.680 --> 00:05:27.720
Could you walk me through
what happened?

86
00:05:29.400 --> 00:05:33.536
Walk? You mean in the house?
That's right.

87
00:05:33.560 --> 00:05:36.640
It could prove vital in stopping him
hurting someone else.

88
00:05:54.400 --> 00:05:57.056
Time sensitive. Up against it here.
Mm.

89
00:05:57.080 --> 00:05:59.616
It's good you've got her back.
That's a rare thing for Monica.

90
00:05:59.640 --> 00:06:01.680
Her partners don't stick around
for long.

91
00:06:02.960 --> 00:06:06.456
I heard she was different
before she had her girl.

92
00:06:06.480 --> 00:06:08.016
Oh. right.

93
00:06:08.040 --> 00:06:11.696
She popped a baby out
and that set her all askew (?)

94
00:06:11.720 --> 00:06:13.816
Seriously?
No. I never meant it like that.

95
00:06:13.840 --> 00:06:15.520
I was just... What?

96
00:06:16.600 --> 00:06:19.616
All coincided with her investigating
the Burning Light. right?

97
00:06:19.640 --> 00:06:21.336
Not that I knew her before.

98
00:06:21.360 --> 00:06:26.440
but from what I gather.
Monica has always... been Monica.

99
00:06:30.960 --> 00:06:33.336
Where would you
watch this house from?

100
00:06:33.360 --> 00:06:35.720
If I was a murdering psychopath?
Yeah.

101
00:06:37.560 --> 00:06:39.280
Nice bit of foliage.

102
00:06:43.160 --> 00:06:44.480
Keep me company?

103
00:06:52.680 --> 00:06:54.216
Start from the beginning.

104
00:06:54.240 --> 00:06:55.656
SCOTT BREATHES SHAKILY

105
00:06:55.680 --> 00:06:57.816
It was... It was there.

106
00:06:57.840 --> 00:07:00.320
That's where you saw him? It.

107
00:07:01.280 --> 00:07:04.016
Nothing seemed human.

108
00:07:04.040 --> 00:07:07.696
Meaning what? It was his face.

109
00:07:07.720 --> 00:07:10.216
It was... BREATHES DEEPLY.

110
00:07:10.240 --> 00:07:12.200
He was wearing a mask?

111
00:07:14.520 --> 00:07:16.000
I need you to describe it.

112
00:07:41.800 --> 00:07:44.096
I prayed you'd return.

113
00:07:44.120 --> 00:07:45.480
HE CHUCKLES DRYLY

114
00:07:47.160 --> 00:07:48.960
So. Jason was taken from in here?

115
00:07:51.760 --> 00:07:55.416
And... both of you are in?

116
00:07:55.440 --> 00:07:57.320
Nichol... Barclay.

117
00:07:58.920 --> 00:08:02.456
You... You prayed to bring him
into our lives. too. didn't you?

118
00:08:02.480 --> 00:08:07.200
When it was just the two of us.
But he never accepted me as his own.

119
00:08:09.560 --> 00:08:11.080
So. what have the police said?

120
00:08:13.440 --> 00:08:15.016
We're waiting on updates.

121
00:08:15.040 --> 00:08:17.896
What. that's it?
What. there's no leads?

122
00:08:17.920 --> 00:08:19.976
I should be asking more.
shouldn't I?

123
00:08:20.000 --> 00:08:22.176
If I'd have been here.
I could have protected him.

124
00:08:22.200 --> 00:08:23.696
But no.

125
00:08:23.720 --> 00:08:26.576
No. I was... I was forced
out of my own home

126
00:08:26.600 --> 00:08:29.696
because you. my own mother.
didn't stand up for me.

127
00:08:29.720 --> 00:08:32.320
Don't.

128
00:08:35.720 --> 00:08:37.976
He was my little brother. Mum.
And...

129
00:08:38.000 --> 00:08:39.440
HORN HONKS OUTSIDE

130
00:08:42.320 --> 00:08:43.480
CAR DOOR SHUTS

131
00:08:50.960 --> 00:08:52.680
Barclay. What?

132
00:08:53.680 --> 00:08:55.800
Don't go mad. but... What?

133
00:09:07.480 --> 00:09:09.640
Alive. then?
Sorry to disappoint.

134
00:09:11.040 --> 00:09:12.176
Why are you here?

135
00:09:12.200 --> 00:09:14.696
Well. because Jason...
Don't say his name.

136
00:09:14.720 --> 00:09:18.640
I will say my brother's name
whenever I want.

137
00:09:23.120 --> 00:09:25.880
When did he get back?
Last night.

138
00:09:27.200 --> 00:09:28.816
You didn't call me.

139
00:09:28.840 --> 00:09:32.120
You still let him speak to you
like that?

140
00:09:42.160 --> 00:09:43.680
Where the fuck have you been?

141
00:09:44.840 --> 00:09:47.560
A lot of... terrible places.

142
00:09:52.160 --> 00:09:53.800
LAUGHS

143
00:09:57.400 --> 00:09:58.480
Hmm.

144
00:10:00.760 --> 00:10:03.440
Well. you're not staying here.
Yes. he is.

145
00:10:04.840 --> 00:10:06.320
He is.

146
00:10:16.360 --> 00:10:19.120
Ever wanted to be a detective?
No.

147
00:10:20.480 --> 00:10:22.360
You'd be good at it. I know.

148
00:10:23.840 --> 00:10:26.256
Christ. do you think I look at you
like you're the Holy Grail?

149
00:10:26.280 --> 00:10:28.840
Oh. you look at me. Carol?
BOTH CHUCKLE.

150
00:10:30.880 --> 00:10:32.616
Places to be? Yeah.

151
00:10:32.640 --> 00:10:35.336
I need to get back to Dwayne
and Johnson.

152
00:10:35.360 --> 00:10:39.336
My black Labs.
Oh. I love Labradors.

153
00:10:39.360 --> 00:10:41.936
I begged for one as a kid. No joy.

154
00:10:41.960 --> 00:10:44.336
Well. you dodged a bullet.
They're a nightmare.

155
00:10:44.360 --> 00:10:46.176
They eat everything.

156
00:10:46.200 --> 00:10:47.456
I spent most of last Christmas

157
00:10:47.480 --> 00:10:49.216
pulling tinsel
out of Dwayne's arsehole.

158
00:10:49.240 --> 00:10:51.280
BOTH LAUGH

159
00:10:54.480 --> 00:10:55.640
Erm...

160
00:10:57.080 --> 00:10:58.920
Good spot to watch from. Yeah.

161
00:11:09.360 --> 00:11:12.176
Something?
Looks like a nicotine pouch.

162
00:11:12.200 --> 00:11:15.720
Yeah. Bingo. Got a poo bag?

163
00:11:32.760 --> 00:11:34.376
Nice one.

164
00:11:34.400 --> 00:11:36.056
MONICA: 'Your mum's working
in France?'

165
00:11:36.080 --> 00:11:38.920
Yeah. she's there more than here.
Always working.

166
00:11:41.760 --> 00:11:43.240
You're home alone a lot. then.

167
00:11:44.800 --> 00:11:47.056
I guess. I've got a job. though.

168
00:11:47.080 --> 00:11:49.240
Doing what?
Bits and bobs for a handyman.

169
00:11:50.960 --> 00:11:55.056
My dad thinks it's important too -
learning the value of money.

170
00:11:55.080 --> 00:11:56.800
Don't tell my mum that.

171
00:11:57.760 --> 00:11:59.896
Why not? She'd go nuts.

172
00:11:59.920 --> 00:12:03.816
I'm not meant to have contact
with him. but he's my dad.

173
00:12:03.840 --> 00:12:06.736
He's not some monster.
like she'd make out.

174
00:12:06.760 --> 00:12:08.800
He's been really trying
since he reached back out.

175
00:12:10.120 --> 00:12:12.696
Fuck. He'll be worried.
I didn't message him back.

176
00:12:12.720 --> 00:12:14.320
Scott. how does he contact you?

177
00:12:17.400 --> 00:12:18.480
Tell me.

178
00:12:20.600 --> 00:12:21.840
The phone he sent me.

179
00:12:23.120 --> 00:12:24.600
Can I see it?

180
00:12:35.080 --> 00:12:36.880
I'll need to hang on to this.

181
00:12:39.600 --> 00:12:41.760
And your regular phone?
You dropped it when you ran?

182
00:12:46.360 --> 00:12:49.376
Went for a stroll.
Assumed he surveyed the house.

183
00:12:49.400 --> 00:12:52.520
Found a nicotine pouch.
Getting DNA fast-tracked.

184
00:12:53.560 --> 00:12:55.040
Any sign of a burner phone?
No sign.

185
00:12:56.200 --> 00:12:58.720
Scott says the killer
wears a pale mask.

186
00:12:59.720 --> 00:13:02.096
Christ. Made from animal skin.
by the sounds of it.

187
00:13:02.120 --> 00:13:03.176
Poor animal.

188
00:13:03.200 --> 00:13:04.696
Hey. Look at this.

189
00:13:04.720 --> 00:13:07.136
Impression of the killer's mask.

190
00:13:07.160 --> 00:13:09.176
What? Why would he wear that?

191
00:13:09.200 --> 00:13:11.336
He wants to terrify his victims.
too?

192
00:13:11.360 --> 00:13:16.816
Well. masks tend to represent desire
to separate identity.

193
00:13:16.840 --> 00:13:19.456
Monster at night. normality by day.

194
00:13:19.480 --> 00:13:21.576
He has a tendency
towards the theatrics.

195
00:13:21.600 --> 00:13:24.896
the staging. taxidermy. the stones.

196
00:13:24.920 --> 00:13:26.616
He wants to be seen.

197
00:13:26.640 --> 00:13:30.176
which leans into the likelihood
that he feels invisible by day.

198
00:13:30.200 --> 00:13:32.280
Educated. frustrated...

199
00:13:33.560 --> 00:13:35.816
plagued by doubts
about his own strength.

200
00:13:35.840 --> 00:13:37.736
hence the need to drug his victims.

201
00:13:37.760 --> 00:13:39.896
Luckily for Scott.
he didn't drink his smoothie.

202
00:13:39.920 --> 00:13:42.176
so he remained conscious.

203
00:13:42.200 --> 00:13:44.616
and the others were easy pickings
for him.

204
00:13:44.640 --> 00:13:46.856
Here. I'll get Carol
to run Scott to the station.

205
00:13:46.880 --> 00:13:48.656
keep an eye on him there
till his mum returns.

206
00:13:48.680 --> 00:13:49.816
PHONE RINGS

207
00:13:49.840 --> 00:13:52.936
Scott was saying something
about staying with some guy. Don.

208
00:13:52.960 --> 00:13:54.056
who he works with.

209
00:13:54.080 --> 00:13:55.936
No. no. best keep him close.

210
00:13:55.960 --> 00:13:57.416
Why don't you ride along with Carol

211
00:13:57.440 --> 00:13:59.096
in case Scott remembers
anything else?

212
00:13:59.120 --> 00:14:01.040
Yeah. sure. I'll catch you there.
See you.

213
00:14:02.600 --> 00:14:04.096
Thanks. mate. See you later.

214
00:14:04.120 --> 00:14:05.440
Nichol's back.

215
00:14:12.560 --> 00:14:14.600
KNOCKING

216
00:14:19.760 --> 00:14:20.856
Can I help you?

217
00:14:20.880 --> 00:14:24.416
Hi. I'm James
from Kintosh Council.

218
00:14:24.440 --> 00:14:25.960
I'm just here to talk about Lucy.

219
00:14:27.000 --> 00:14:31.000
Erm. are you here about
that "poisoning tummies" nonsense?

220
00:14:32.120 --> 00:14:34.016
I mean. I don't understand

221
00:14:34.040 --> 00:14:36.696
how this meeting was allowed
to happen

222
00:14:36.720 --> 00:14:38.376
without us being told about it.

223
00:14:38.400 --> 00:14:41.040
Don't worry.
It's just standard practice.

224
00:14:42.200 --> 00:14:44.616
The school flag
when they think a kid is vulnerable.

225
00:14:44.640 --> 00:14:47.976
and then. hey. presto. me.
assigned social worker.

226
00:14:48.000 --> 00:14:49.336
Vulnerable?

227
00:14:49.360 --> 00:14:52.216
Does Lucy have access to harmful
material around the house?

228
00:14:52.240 --> 00:14:53.840
Files of her mum's cases?

229
00:14:54.800 --> 00:14:57.240
Of course not. OK.

230
00:14:58.200 --> 00:14:59.520
What else do you need to know?

231
00:15:01.280 --> 00:15:03.456
Well. honestly.
just a tiny bit more.

232
00:15:03.480 --> 00:15:04.680
Erm...

233
00:15:05.720 --> 00:15:08.336
Sorry.
why is Lucy not at school today?

234
00:15:08.360 --> 00:15:10.920
Oh. she wasn't feeling very well.

235
00:15:12.080 --> 00:15:15.096
She doesn't look too unwell to me.
That's kids for you.

236
00:15:15.120 --> 00:15:18.416
So resilient. they just bounce back.
Yeah.

237
00:15:18.440 --> 00:15:20.216
And how's your resilience?

238
00:15:20.240 --> 00:15:22.936
How are you coping with Lucy?

239
00:15:22.960 --> 00:15:26.080
I don't "cope" with her.
I'm her grandmother. I love her.

240
00:15:27.280 --> 00:15:28.656
As does her mother.

241
00:15:28.680 --> 00:15:31.736
Oh. yeah. Monica. CHUCKLES

242
00:15:31.760 --> 00:15:33.040
I've had the pleasure.

243
00:15:34.600 --> 00:15:36.760
Lucy. do you wanna come over
and have a chat?

244
00:15:37.920 --> 00:15:40.256
It's all right. sweetheart.
Yeah?

245
00:15:40.280 --> 00:15:42.856
There you go.
Do you remember me? I'm James.

246
00:15:42.880 --> 00:15:45.136
I asked you a couple of questions
last time we met.

247
00:15:45.160 --> 00:15:47.800
I remember you. Yeah.

248
00:15:49.400 --> 00:15:52.136
Yeah. Oh. Good girl.

249
00:15:52.160 --> 00:15:53.520
CHUCKLES

250
00:16:18.800 --> 00:16:20.640
What's he doing here?

251
00:16:22.320 --> 00:16:26.000
This is your doing. You called him?
He knew him best.

252
00:16:33.440 --> 00:16:35.856
Looks like there's a difference
of opinion on me being here.

253
00:16:35.880 --> 00:16:37.016
Yeah. huge one.

254
00:16:37.040 --> 00:16:38.816
This... This is mad.
Maybe you're right.

255
00:16:38.840 --> 00:16:40.760
Me being here's a mistake.

256
00:16:49.160 --> 00:16:50.360
Hello. Michael.

257
00:16:54.000 --> 00:16:55.160
I thought the worst.

258
00:16:56.520 --> 00:16:59.016
Buried in a ditch
or at the bottom of a loch.

259
00:16:59.040 --> 00:17:03.376
God. Michael. I had no idea.
I'm... I'm so sorry.

260
00:17:03.400 --> 00:17:09.936
I had... gotten so scared that all
I felt like I could do was run.

261
00:17:09.960 --> 00:17:13.056
Where? I went to London.

262
00:17:13.080 --> 00:17:17.536
It's very easy to disappear there.
You know. streets. hostels.

263
00:17:17.560 --> 00:17:19.600
What made you so scared
that you ran?

264
00:17:27.680 --> 00:17:31.176
Barclay... ruled through love
and hate.

265
00:17:31.200 --> 00:17:34.336
Jason. his real son. got the love.
I got the hate. OK?

266
00:17:34.360 --> 00:17:36.760
And it just got too much for me.
That must be hard.

267
00:17:40.600 --> 00:17:42.656
It wasn't you I saw
on the television.

268
00:17:42.680 --> 00:17:44.376
It was another woman talking
about Jason.

269
00:17:44.400 --> 00:17:47.400
I'm leading the investigation.
Oh. and it's gone where. exactly?

270
00:17:48.600 --> 00:17:51.536
Any suspects?
Hopefully. you can help me.

271
00:17:51.560 --> 00:17:52.760
LAUGHS

272
00:17:54.040 --> 00:17:55.360
Oh. me?

273
00:17:56.720 --> 00:17:58.376
OK. Right.

274
00:17:58.400 --> 00:18:01.640
Well. I am your hope
at solving this. am I?

275
00:18:03.280 --> 00:18:05.776
My little brother was killed.
Michael...

276
00:18:05.800 --> 00:18:06.896
No. You know what?

277
00:18:06.920 --> 00:18:10.200
I have so many what-ifs
running around in my head.

278
00:18:12.480 --> 00:18:15.736
You know. like.
"What if I'd have stayed?

279
00:18:15.760 --> 00:18:18.080
"Maybe I could have
protected Jason." But...

280
00:18:19.840 --> 00:18:22.336
Before you left.
you had a black stone.

281
00:18:22.360 --> 00:18:23.416
A stone? Yes.

282
00:18:23.440 --> 00:18:26.336
Yeah. the last few times we talked.
you were holding one.

283
00:18:26.360 --> 00:18:29.040
You. er... You kissed it.

284
00:18:31.200 --> 00:18:32.360
Do you mean like this?

285
00:18:36.000 --> 00:18:37.776
These were wishing stones.

286
00:18:37.800 --> 00:18:40.480
I always carry one with me.
a lucky charm.

287
00:18:41.560 --> 00:18:43.296
If it's important.
you can have it.

288
00:18:43.320 --> 00:18:45.696
Are they linked to the murders?

289
00:18:45.720 --> 00:18:47.776
We think so.

290
00:18:47.800 --> 00:18:49.160
Do you know Owen MacLennan?

291
00:18:51.000 --> 00:18:56.080
No. Mum works for the family.
He died the night before last.

292
00:18:59.560 --> 00:19:00.600
Died?

293
00:19:03.480 --> 00:19:06.360
Is it the person that...
killed Jason?

294
00:19:07.520 --> 00:19:11.600
We found a photo of you inside
a taxidermied rabbit in his room.

295
00:19:12.760 --> 00:19:13.800
Wh...?

296
00:19:15.720 --> 00:19:19.576
Me? What. in a... in a rabbit?

297
00:19:19.600 --> 00:19:21.496
It wasn't just your photo.

298
00:19:21.520 --> 00:19:24.816
It was Jason's. Robert Wright's
and an intended victim's.

299
00:19:24.840 --> 00:19:26.736
Well. why would my photo
be with theirs?

300
00:19:26.760 --> 00:19:28.920
You have no idea?

301
00:19:30.840 --> 00:19:32.840
No. I... What. me?

302
00:19:34.960 --> 00:19:36.536
No. HE SCOFFS.

303
00:19:36.560 --> 00:19:38.160
Where were you last night?

304
00:19:40.600 --> 00:19:42.736
I was here with my mum.

305
00:19:42.760 --> 00:19:44.896
SCOTT: 'Let me out! Let me out!'
DHILLON: 'Scott...'

306
00:19:44.920 --> 00:19:47.096
I wanted to go to Don's house.
not with you. All right.

307
00:19:47.120 --> 00:19:49.320
I promise you. bud.
You're OK. you're OK.

308
00:19:50.320 --> 00:19:52.976
Come on. mate. Just deep breaths.
Deep breaths. Come on.

309
00:19:53.000 --> 00:19:54.736
SCOTT HYPERVENTILATING

310
00:19:54.760 --> 00:19:56.456
Police can't even stop shoplifters.

311
00:19:56.480 --> 00:19:58.896
I mean. rightly. you're upset.
but... How much further?

312
00:19:58.920 --> 00:20:01.336
It's about 20 minutes.
Scott. you are safe.

313
00:20:01.360 --> 00:20:03.920
Scott. did you hear that?
It's just 20 minutes.

314
00:20:05.360 --> 00:20:07.016
Erm...

315
00:20:07.040 --> 00:20:08.576
I'm bursting.

316
00:20:08.600 --> 00:20:10.720
Yeah. OK.
Looks a bit dry down there.

317
00:20:17.080 --> 00:20:20.376
So. do you believe him?
Do you think he's involved?

318
00:20:20.400 --> 00:20:22.000
What. you still trust my judgement?

319
00:20:23.440 --> 00:20:25.776
The way I spoke to you.
blaming you...

320
00:20:25.800 --> 00:20:27.976
Look. I don't know
if I'll agree with your opinion.

321
00:20:28.000 --> 00:20:30.616
but I want to hear it.
HE EXHALES

322
00:20:30.640 --> 00:20:32.776
I made the stones
into this huge thing.

323
00:20:32.800 --> 00:20:34.536
and he was just there
with one in his hand.

324
00:20:34.560 --> 00:20:37.320
So. do you believe him?
That he doesn't know anything?

325
00:20:40.720 --> 00:20:42.176
Look. he was...

326
00:20:42.200 --> 00:20:44.680
He's not the boy I remember.

327
00:20:46.040 --> 00:20:47.680
But that's what grief does.

328
00:20:52.040 --> 00:20:53.280
So. yeah.

329
00:20:54.760 --> 00:20:55.976
I believe him.

330
00:20:56.000 --> 00:20:58.120
OK. Still. let's keep an eye on him.

331
00:21:03.000 --> 00:21:04.976
All right. mate.
Yeah. we're heading your way.

332
00:21:05.000 --> 00:21:07.336
Oh. about... about that.

333
00:21:07.360 --> 00:21:09.416
There's...
There's a bit of an issue.

334
00:21:09.440 --> 00:21:10.616
OK. Spill.

335
00:21:10.640 --> 00:21:12.976
So. Scott freaked out.

336
00:21:13.000 --> 00:21:15.576
and. erm. he needed
to go out for a wee...

337
00:21:15.600 --> 00:21:17.176
and he's legged it.

338
00:21:17.200 --> 00:21:18.896
Not serious?

339
00:21:18.920 --> 00:21:21.736
'We've searched the woods nearby...'
Shit.

340
00:21:21.760 --> 00:21:24.160
Er. they've lost Scott.

341
00:21:25.520 --> 00:21:27.360
You're on loudspeaker to Kennedy.

342
00:21:28.760 --> 00:21:31.856
Hadid. Hit on the DNA
from your tobacco pouch.

343
00:21:31.880 --> 00:21:34.776
Don Cameron.
As in Roderick Cameron's son?

344
00:21:34.800 --> 00:21:37.496
Scott said something
about staying with a Don.

345
00:21:37.520 --> 00:21:39.976
A handyman he works for.
"Handyman"?

346
00:21:40.000 --> 00:21:43.336
That's a euphemism and a half
for a family of guns for hire.

347
00:21:43.360 --> 00:21:46.176
The Camerons live not far from here.

348
00:21:46.200 --> 00:21:49.536
We could go knock.
see if Scott's headed there.

349
00:21:49.560 --> 00:21:52.256
No. That family's history.
there may be weapons on site.

350
00:21:52.280 --> 00:21:56.136
Just... head there. get some eyes
on the house and wait for us.

351
00:21:56.160 --> 00:21:57.696
'We'll call for back-up.' OK.

352
00:21:57.720 --> 00:21:59.016
Y-Yes. Ma'am.

353
00:21:59.040 --> 00:22:01.600
BREATHING HEAVILY

354
00:22:08.600 --> 00:22:10.920
BREATHING SHAKILY

355
00:22:31.080 --> 00:22:32.800
UNDER BREATH: Come on.

356
00:22:35.120 --> 00:22:36.800
Come on.

357
00:22:43.440 --> 00:22:44.880
HE SOBS

358
00:22:47.800 --> 00:22:49.960
SOBBING

359
00:23:08.600 --> 00:23:10.320
KNOCK AT DOOR

360
00:23:46.320 --> 00:23:47.800
Down here.

361
00:23:48.760 --> 00:23:50.400
Something to warm you.

362
00:24:03.440 --> 00:24:06.576
COMMENTARY ON TV

363
00:24:06.600 --> 00:24:08.680
RODERICK: Flukey bastard!

364
00:24:13.360 --> 00:24:15.136
TV: 'That is clinical.'

365
00:24:15.160 --> 00:24:17.080
Come on. boy.

366
00:24:19.440 --> 00:24:23.416
Police are treating me like a baby.
Got me all locked up and everything.

367
00:24:23.440 --> 00:24:24.880
Snuck away?

368
00:24:27.160 --> 00:24:29.136
Is that a problem? No.

369
00:24:29.160 --> 00:24:30.936
RODERICK: Jesus Christ!

370
00:24:30.960 --> 00:24:32.976
RODERICK COUGHING

371
00:24:33.000 --> 00:24:34.760
Likes his snooker. eh?

372
00:24:36.880 --> 00:24:38.200
Yeah.

373
00:24:44.480 --> 00:24:45.760
Scott?

374
00:24:48.040 --> 00:24:49.576
Can stay.

375
00:24:49.600 --> 00:24:51.120
Be safe here.

376
00:24:53.120 --> 00:24:56.136
Wash up. Bathroom's along the way.

377
00:24:56.160 --> 00:24:58.976
RODERICK: Is that tea
coming yet. eh?

378
00:24:59.000 --> 00:25:00.880
COUGHING

379
00:25:08.200 --> 00:25:11.896
RODERICK CHUNTERING

380
00:25:11.920 --> 00:25:13.656
COUGHING

381
00:25:13.680 --> 00:25:15.320
Oh. Jesus.

382
00:25:27.360 --> 00:25:29.240
PHONE RINGS

383
00:25:45.720 --> 00:25:48.816
Er. there's no sign of Scott.

384
00:25:48.840 --> 00:25:50.600
Back-up should be here soon.

385
00:26:00.680 --> 00:26:02.200
RODERICK: Black!

386
00:26:03.240 --> 00:26:06.600
RODDERICK CACKLING. COUGHING

387
00:26:09.800 --> 00:26:11.496
I opened the wrong door.

388
00:26:11.520 --> 00:26:13.040
Sorry.

389
00:26:14.600 --> 00:26:16.456
You can ask me.

390
00:26:16.480 --> 00:26:17.936
The photo.

391
00:26:17.960 --> 00:26:19.720
It's OK. I pried.

392
00:26:22.240 --> 00:26:24.616
RODERICK: Water!
Do you need to check on him?

393
00:26:24.640 --> 00:26:26.400
COUGHING

394
00:26:32.080 --> 00:26:33.920
My broth will be getting cold.

395
00:26:44.360 --> 00:26:46.440
Come on. boy...

396
00:26:51.640 --> 00:26:52.656
Scott?

397
00:26:52.680 --> 00:26:55.200
Wait! Let me explain.

398
00:26:59.440 --> 00:27:02.096
To Don and the other...
There's movement.

399
00:27:02.120 --> 00:27:03.160
Shit.

400
00:27:05.360 --> 00:27:07.096
Scott!

401
00:27:07.120 --> 00:27:08.696
He's got my phone!

402
00:27:08.720 --> 00:27:10.656
SCOTT PANTING

403
00:27:10.680 --> 00:27:12.880
It's Don. isn't it? He's the killer.

404
00:27:14.480 --> 00:27:15.976
You're safe. Get yourself in here.

405
00:27:16.000 --> 00:27:18.520
CRAWFORD: All right.
Get in there. Here you go.

406
00:27:22.960 --> 00:27:25.360
Oh. Christ. What is he doing?

407
00:27:31.320 --> 00:27:32.696
Are his arms still raised?

408
00:27:32.720 --> 00:27:35.056
This is totally against protocol.

409
00:27:35.080 --> 00:27:37.520
We should be waiting for back-up.
'Crawford.'

410
00:27:38.760 --> 00:27:40.376
Yes. still raised.

411
00:27:40.400 --> 00:27:44.616
Don? My name's
Detective Inspector Kennedy.

412
00:27:44.640 --> 00:27:46.976
I'm gonna need you to step out
with your arms raised.

413
00:27:47.000 --> 00:27:48.240
Can you do that for me?

414
00:27:50.960 --> 00:27:54.376
Can you say you understand for me?
I understand.

415
00:27:54.400 --> 00:27:57.200
On three. Nice and calm.

416
00:27:58.440 --> 00:28:02.520
One... two... three.

417
00:28:22.080 --> 00:28:24.200
Thank you. Perfect.

418
00:28:25.680 --> 00:28:27.520
I'm gonna approach now. Don.

419
00:28:31.880 --> 00:28:33.736
Come on. Kennedy.

420
00:28:33.760 --> 00:28:36.200
Now turn around
with your hands on your head.

421
00:28:37.800 --> 00:28:40.040
HANDCUFFS CLINK

422
00:28:43.560 --> 00:28:45.240
Taking your right wrist now.

423
00:28:46.960 --> 00:28:48.560
That's it. Nice and easy.

424
00:28:49.880 --> 00:28:51.856
Now your left.

425
00:28:51.880 --> 00:28:53.160
Nice and easy.

426
00:28:55.160 --> 00:28:56.720
OK.

427
00:29:09.680 --> 00:29:11.936
Said nothing? Mm.

428
00:29:11.960 --> 00:29:14.896
Anyone else in the property?
Just Don's father.

429
00:29:14.920 --> 00:29:17.576
I'm gonna see what he can tell us
about Don's movements last night.

430
00:29:17.600 --> 00:29:19.056
I'm gonna have a look around.

431
00:29:19.080 --> 00:29:21.120
I reckon this sick bastard
keeps trophies.

432
00:29:24.560 --> 00:29:26.736
Maybe you'll get back
to your Labs after all.

433
00:29:26.760 --> 00:29:28.136
Be a drink I need.

434
00:29:28.160 --> 00:29:29.800
Is that an invite?

435
00:29:31.080 --> 00:29:33.936
Statement. Oh. semantics.

436
00:29:33.960 --> 00:29:35.600
THEY LAUGH

437
00:29:41.000 --> 00:29:43.176
COMMENTARY ON TV

438
00:29:43.200 --> 00:29:45.256
Roderick. it's the police.

439
00:29:45.280 --> 00:29:47.936
Not senile.

440
00:29:47.960 --> 00:29:50.216
Or fucking blind.

441
00:29:50.240 --> 00:29:52.856
TV: 'Playing with real purpose now.'

442
00:29:52.880 --> 00:29:54.800
You gonna stand there all day?

443
00:29:56.280 --> 00:29:57.880
'Beautiful cue action.

444
00:29:59.040 --> 00:30:01.976
'These two players
aren't giving an inch.

445
00:30:02.000 --> 00:30:03.856
'as we saw in the round of 16.'

446
00:30:03.880 --> 00:30:06.496
Mind if I turn the TV off?

447
00:30:06.520 --> 00:30:08.120
I know how it ends.

448
00:30:13.720 --> 00:30:15.176
Don's in a lot of trouble.

449
00:30:15.200 --> 00:30:17.840
Time is neither of our friend.

450
00:30:19.480 --> 00:30:22.216
Ask your question.
Was Don here last night?

451
00:30:22.240 --> 00:30:26.176
If every question's a memory test.
you're doomed wi' me.

452
00:30:26.200 --> 00:30:28.096
Better with names?

453
00:30:28.120 --> 00:30:29.696
Jason Morgan?

454
00:30:29.720 --> 00:30:32.056
Robert Wright? Owen MacLennan?

455
00:30:32.080 --> 00:30:34.136
All dead. I guess?

456
00:30:34.160 --> 00:30:37.016
Been watching the news.
not just snooker reruns. then.

457
00:30:37.040 --> 00:30:38.936
HE COUGHS

458
00:30:38.960 --> 00:30:40.376
Sorry.

459
00:30:40.400 --> 00:30:42.776
Names. Pure fog.

460
00:30:42.800 --> 00:30:45.016
Scott MacKay? Hm?

461
00:30:45.040 --> 00:30:47.656
Trickster. He's alive.

462
00:30:47.680 --> 00:30:50.056
Heard his voice only minutes ago.

463
00:30:50.080 --> 00:30:52.896
The serial killer
targeted him last night.

464
00:30:52.920 --> 00:30:55.056
Evidence points
to Don being on the scene.

465
00:30:55.080 --> 00:30:56.896
Scott's convinced too.

466
00:30:56.920 --> 00:30:58.400
HE CHUCKLES SOFTLY

467
00:31:16.840 --> 00:31:19.056
Odd boy. my Don.

468
00:31:19.080 --> 00:31:20.480
Funny way about him.

469
00:31:21.800 --> 00:31:23.520
Still. he went very quietly.

470
00:31:27.600 --> 00:31:29.360
You don't think Don's a killer?

471
00:31:31.920 --> 00:31:34.920
Oh. Don could kill. all right.

472
00:31:36.440 --> 00:31:39.336
A lot's been written about you.
Roderick.

473
00:31:39.360 --> 00:31:42.880
Must be sad when it's only
the obituary left to do.

474
00:31:45.320 --> 00:31:48.336
Always time for one last chapter.

475
00:31:48.360 --> 00:31:50.336
FOOTSTEPS APPROACH

476
00:31:50.360 --> 00:31:53.440
DHILLON: Here. Kennedy.
You need to see this.

477
00:32:08.040 --> 00:32:11.776
Have a license for these? No.

478
00:32:11.800 --> 00:32:16.240
Aw. look at his little heart.
all a-jingling.

479
00:32:17.400 --> 00:32:18.760
Relax.

480
00:32:20.720 --> 00:32:23.120
They're long deactivated.

481
00:32:24.160 --> 00:32:26.480
Just memories they hold now.

482
00:32:29.160 --> 00:32:30.776
Do us a tea.

483
00:32:30.800 --> 00:32:32.896
In the pot.

484
00:32:32.920 --> 00:32:35.616
No. Oh...

485
00:32:35.640 --> 00:32:37.536
HE CHUCKLES SOFTLY

486
00:32:37.560 --> 00:32:39.200
Mean boy.

487
00:32:40.360 --> 00:32:42.416
Look like a nice lass.

488
00:32:42.440 --> 00:32:43.696
Agh!

489
00:32:43.720 --> 00:32:45.560
HE CHUCKLES

490
00:32:47.120 --> 00:32:48.760
HE COUGHS

491
00:32:54.560 --> 00:32:57.040
Fresh lock. Sourcing some cutters.

492
00:33:00.200 --> 00:33:02.016
Ah.

493
00:33:02.040 --> 00:33:06.480
Kindness... never gets forgot.

494
00:33:11.960 --> 00:33:13.000
Oh.

495
00:33:14.120 --> 00:33:15.320
Thank you.

496
00:33:18.680 --> 00:33:20.856
There's a locked cellar outside.

497
00:33:20.880 --> 00:33:24.416
Oh. Is that so?

498
00:33:24.440 --> 00:33:26.816
It won't take us long to unlock it

499
00:33:26.840 --> 00:33:30.056
so might as well tell us
what we'll find.

500
00:33:30.080 --> 00:33:31.976
Maybe...

501
00:33:32.000 --> 00:33:34.696
SHOUTING: it's
the fucking treasure I buried

502
00:33:34.720 --> 00:33:38.080
when I wasn't hooked up
to these fucking tanks!

503
00:33:40.560 --> 00:33:42.616
HE WHEEZES

504
00:33:42.640 --> 00:33:44.536
Only kidding...

505
00:33:44.560 --> 00:33:46.120
boy.

506
00:33:47.640 --> 00:33:51.800
Maybe the goodies
my Don likes to hide away.

507
00:33:58.680 --> 00:34:00.160
Custard cream?

508
00:34:34.920 --> 00:34:36.960
Gun! SHE GRUNTS.

509
00:34:40.840 --> 00:34:43.000
RODERICK CACKLING.
DHILLON GROANS

510
00:34:46.520 --> 00:34:48.696
Gun! RODERICK ROARS.

511
00:34:48.720 --> 00:34:51.376
Fuck off! Officers down!

512
00:34:51.400 --> 00:34:55.536
Ah. you bastard police.
coming into my place!

513
00:34:55.560 --> 00:34:58.080
DHILLON BREATHING RAPIDLY

514
00:34:59.280 --> 00:35:01.536
Carol? Carol? Hey...

515
00:35:01.560 --> 00:35:03.856
Look at me. Look at me.
I've got you. I've got you.

516
00:35:03.880 --> 00:35:05.896
It's gonna be all right. No. no. no.

517
00:35:05.920 --> 00:35:07.536
Don't close your eyes on me. pal.
No. no.

518
00:35:07.560 --> 00:35:09.656
Urgent assistance.
Urgent assistance needed.

519
00:35:09.680 --> 00:35:11.576
Shut up! Shut him up!

520
00:35:11.600 --> 00:35:15.296
DC Connor Crawford.
Urgent assistance needed. er...

521
00:35:15.320 --> 00:35:17.376
East Blaric Farm.
East Blaric Farm.

522
00:35:17.400 --> 00:35:19.856
Two officers down.
Stay with me. mate. Stay with me.

523
00:35:19.880 --> 00:35:21.256
Yeah. two officers down.

524
00:35:21.280 --> 00:35:24.296
Gunshot wounds.
One unresponsive. one severe.

525
00:35:24.320 --> 00:35:25.816
Your full support needed.

526
00:35:25.840 --> 00:35:28.376
Just breathe.
Here we go. Sorry. pal. Hey. hey!

527
00:35:28.400 --> 00:35:30.456
Hey. Carol. Carol. Carol.
Hey! No. no.

528
00:35:30.480 --> 00:35:32.760
Come on. pal. stay with me.
Help's on its way. all right?

529
00:35:38.800 --> 00:35:41.280
POLICE RADIO CHATTER

530
00:36:45.440 --> 00:36:46.560
Up.

531
00:36:49.320 --> 00:36:51.376
Fine. be no use. Monica!

532
00:36:51.400 --> 00:36:53.360
We should have waited for back-up.

533
00:36:56.600 --> 00:36:58.640
I'm just going to sit with you.

534
00:37:28.480 --> 00:37:30.240
ENGINE STARTS

535
00:37:56.000 --> 00:37:57.696
Found mine near Scott's. then.

536
00:37:57.720 --> 00:38:00.240
So you're not denying
you were there.

537
00:38:02.520 --> 00:38:04.096
What were you doing there. Don?

538
00:38:04.120 --> 00:38:05.736
Watching?

539
00:38:05.760 --> 00:38:08.576
Like with Rob Wright and Jason?

540
00:38:08.600 --> 00:38:10.336
Scott was by himself.

541
00:38:10.360 --> 00:38:13.736
Mum left him. No dad to protect him.

542
00:38:13.760 --> 00:38:15.776
So you were there to do that?

543
00:38:15.800 --> 00:38:18.536
The news said
to keep men like Scott safe.

544
00:38:18.560 --> 00:38:20.816
RADIO: 'Detective Kennedy.
we need you to pull in...'

545
00:38:20.840 --> 00:38:22.896
SHE SWITCHES RADIO OFF

546
00:38:22.920 --> 00:38:25.416
They think you're driving
to drown me in a loch.

547
00:38:25.440 --> 00:38:27.336
Who said I'm not? The road.

548
00:38:27.360 --> 00:38:29.280
Route to your station.

549
00:38:30.840 --> 00:38:33.056
I'm not who you're looking for.

550
00:38:33.080 --> 00:38:37.136
Scott's phone in your possession.
DNA linking you to the scene.

551
00:38:37.160 --> 00:38:39.760
Your dad won't cut it as an alibi.

552
00:38:40.800 --> 00:38:42.536
I have a son.

553
00:38:42.560 --> 00:38:46.976
Last night. I was visiting my boy.
Where?

554
00:38:47.000 --> 00:38:51.520
His grave. All Wells Church.
There's CCTV.

555
00:38:56.560 --> 00:38:58.456
So you weren't there
when Scott was attacked?

556
00:38:58.480 --> 00:39:00.800
Think your man would be alive
if I was?

557
00:39:06.440 --> 00:39:08.376
I went to check on Scott
this morning.

558
00:39:08.400 --> 00:39:11.336
I saw the police
and kept my distance.

559
00:39:11.360 --> 00:39:12.976
That's when I found his phone.

560
00:39:13.000 --> 00:39:15.376
I must have dropped
a nicotine patch.

561
00:39:15.400 --> 00:39:17.120
PHONE BEEPS

562
00:39:41.000 --> 00:39:43.056
Are you OK. love? Hungry?

563
00:39:43.080 --> 00:39:46.496
I'll be through to do tea in five.
This has been a wee bit fiddly.

564
00:39:46.520 --> 00:39:47.696
Did you put my bag in the boot?

565
00:39:47.720 --> 00:39:49.536
I'll bring it in. hon.
It's fine. You're busy.

566
00:39:49.560 --> 00:39:51.800
Just let me finish this.
It's a bit oily.

567
00:39:58.480 --> 00:40:00.280
Tammy?

568
00:40:03.120 --> 00:40:06.456
You OK? Yeah. Yeah.

569
00:40:06.480 --> 00:40:09.960
OK. Come on. My bike can wait.
Let's get tea on.

570
00:40:18.560 --> 00:40:20.096
Don't fall for this act.

571
00:40:20.120 --> 00:40:22.440
He's the same snake he always was.

572
00:40:47.360 --> 00:40:48.680
Get him booked.

573
00:40:50.040 --> 00:40:53.256
Every protocol.
all of his rights...

574
00:40:53.280 --> 00:40:54.696
you've undermined them.

575
00:40:54.720 --> 00:40:57.216
Even a shite solicitor
could shred our case.

576
00:40:57.240 --> 00:40:58.496
Irrelevant.

577
00:40:58.520 --> 00:41:00.216
Irrelevant?
Don's not the killer.

578
00:41:00.240 --> 00:41:03.056
DNA has him at the scene.

579
00:41:03.080 --> 00:41:05.136
He was in possession
of Scott's phone.

580
00:41:05.160 --> 00:41:08.256
Don doesn't fit the profile.
Limited education.

581
00:41:08.280 --> 00:41:10.616
He works and lives in nature.
not at a desk.

582
00:41:10.640 --> 00:41:12.816
He believes in the fairness
of the hunt. He'd never...

583
00:41:12.840 --> 00:41:14.216
All I'm hearing is theory.

584
00:41:14.240 --> 00:41:15.856
Where's your evidence?

585
00:41:15.880 --> 00:41:17.656
Give me one fact.

586
00:41:17.680 --> 00:41:20.576
Go check the CCTV
at All Wells Church last night.

587
00:41:20.600 --> 00:41:22.936
Don visiting his son's grave.

588
00:41:22.960 --> 00:41:24.376
Hold him till his alibi checks out.

589
00:41:24.400 --> 00:41:27.056
but in the meantime.
the killer's still out there.

590
00:41:27.080 --> 00:41:30.536
You've made a complete mess of this.
Monica. Where are we now?

591
00:41:30.560 --> 00:41:33.176
An officer dead.
Dhillon seriously ill.

592
00:41:33.200 --> 00:41:35.176
Neighbours suspicious of neighbours.

593
00:41:35.200 --> 00:41:37.320
All for what? Another dead end.

594
00:41:38.440 --> 00:41:40.360
Please tell me you've got something.

595
00:41:42.800 --> 00:41:44.256
SHE SIGHS
Then we need fresh eyes.

596
00:41:44.280 --> 00:41:47.016
By the time you draft someone else
in. there'll be another boy dead.

597
00:41:47.040 --> 00:41:48.856
Your statement will need taking.

598
00:41:48.880 --> 00:41:50.296
A welfare assessment.

599
00:41:50.320 --> 00:41:53.296
Or you could turn around
and I'll walk away.

600
00:41:53.320 --> 00:41:54.840
PHONE BUZZES

601
00:41:58.240 --> 00:42:00.880
This is your last chance. Monica.

602
00:42:19.040 --> 00:42:20.456
Kennedy. wh-where are you going?

603
00:42:20.480 --> 00:42:22.376
Don's inside. Not him.

604
00:42:22.400 --> 00:42:25.536
What do you mean. not him?
Go inside. It'll be explained.

605
00:42:25.560 --> 00:42:28.016
Where are you going?
They'll want your statement too.

606
00:42:28.040 --> 00:42:30.616
What sort of an answer is that?
Go. do it. then go home.

607
00:42:30.640 --> 00:42:34.440
Hey. Carol's dead. Yes.

608
00:42:35.800 --> 00:42:38.256
I'm sorry. Th-That's it?

609
00:42:38.280 --> 00:42:40.096
You...

610
00:42:40.120 --> 00:42:42.736
You know.
everyone warned me about you.

611
00:42:42.760 --> 00:42:47.296
"You get nothing from her.
She is cold. remote. a robot."

612
00:42:47.320 --> 00:42:49.696
And I've tried to prove them wrong.
but they were right.

613
00:42:49.720 --> 00:42:51.656
Cos here you are.
you're shutting me.

614
00:42:51.680 --> 00:42:55.176
shutting everyone else out.
everyone bar Michael Bach.

615
00:42:55.200 --> 00:42:58.136
I mean. a fucking suspect!

616
00:42:58.160 --> 00:43:01.656
And how is that panning out for you?
Are you closer to catching him?

617
00:43:01.680 --> 00:43:03.736
You're not cut out for this.
Crawford.

618
00:43:03.760 --> 00:43:06.256
Fuck you. Kennedy.
There's places you just can't go.

619
00:43:06.280 --> 00:43:09.000
Yeah. you're right. and
a batshit cult would be one of them.

620
00:43:13.600 --> 00:43:15.600
PHONE BEEPS

621
00:43:28.440 --> 00:43:31.040
WIND BLOWS. LEAVES RUSTLE

622
00:43:33.960 --> 00:43:36.360
OWL HOOTS

623
00:43:40.000 --> 00:43:42.800
WIND CHIMES TINKLING

624
00:44:30.240 --> 00:44:32.120
PHONE BEEPS

625
00:44:47.840 --> 00:44:49.560
PHONE BEEPS

626
00:44:52.600 --> 00:44:55.800
FOOTSTEPS APPROACH

627
00:45:02.680 --> 00:45:03.776
Monica.

628
00:45:03.800 --> 00:45:05.696
Philly.

629
00:45:05.720 --> 00:45:08.440
What are you doing here?
You came back.

630
00:45:15.600 --> 00:45:17.640
Subtitles by accessibility@itv.com
